# Mobile-first and Responsive

- Always build UI mobile-first: base styles target small screens; progressively enhance with breakpoints (`sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`, `2xl`).
- The webapp must deliver an excellent experience on both mobile and desktop: verify layout, spacing, readability, and interactions at each breakpoint.
- Prefer responsive utilities (e.g., `grid`, `flex`, `w-full`, `max-w-*`) and avoid fixed pixel widths except for large containers.
- Ensure accessible touch targets (mín. 44x44px) and keyboard/focus states across devices.
- Avoid hover-only interactions; provide click/active/focus alternatives.
- Optimize images and assets for small screens by default; upscale responsibly on larger screens.
